<refentry id="bif.AddStrategy" xreflabel="AddStrategy">

<refmeta>
<indexterm>
<primary>AddStrategy</primary>
</indexterm>

<refentrytitle>AddStrategy</refentrytitle>
<refmiscinfo>Built-in function</refmiscinfo>
</refmeta>

<refnamediv>
<refname>AddStrategy</refname>
<refpurpose>
Adds a strategy to a support
</refpurpose>
</refnamediv>

<refsynopsisdiv>
<synopsis>
AddStrategy[support->NFSUPPORT, strategy->STRATEGY] =: NFSUPPORT 
</synopsis>
</refsynopsisdiv>

<refsect1><title>Description</title>
<para>
<function>AddStrategy</function> adds <parameter>strategy</parameter>
to the <parameter>support</parameter>.  If the strategy is already in
the support, no change is made.  A copy of the modified support is
returned.  It is an error if <parameter>support</parameter> and
<parameter>strategy</parameter> are not from the same normal form
game.
</para>
</refsect1>

<refsect1><title>See also</title>
